<tr><td bgcolor="#3F403F" width="98%" class="cheader"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="84d2b1152e98cb77a826b3278db9feed" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magic/articles/articles.php'>Video Games and Movies</option><option value='/wars/articles/articles.php'>Wizards Minis</option></select></td></form></tr></table></td><td bgcolor="3F403F" valign="top" align="right" width="22"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/topcorner.gif" width="23" height="22" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0" align="right"></td></tr>
<tr><td width="98%" colspan=2><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" class="cbody">
<tr><td><font class="h1font"> V Set 10 Vader and Darth Vader&#39;s Lightsaber<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.60)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=175'>Scott "CRingwell" Lingrell</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=175&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> July 12, 2005</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Darth Vader&#39;s Lightsaber (V)<br />
Deploy on Vader.  May add 1 to Force drain where present.  May target a Jedi or Skywalker for free.  Draw 3 destiny and choose 2.  Target hit (may place any Interrupt from opponent&#39;s Lost Pile out of play) and forfeit = 0, if total destiny > ability.<br />
<br />
Finally, Darth Vader is getting the Jedi-hating support he deserves.  This lightsaber is without a doubt one of the most powerful in the game.  Drawing 3 and choosing 2 gives you VERY good odds of hitting your target, and when you hit something you get to place an Interrupt from opponent&#39;s lost pile out of play.  All of this, and it can still add to Force drain and make the target forfeit = 0!<br />
<br />
The downside to the saber, of course, is that it can only target Jedi or Skywalkers.  As such, a great combo is to put this lightsaber on Darth Vader, Dark Lord Of The Sith.  This allows you to choke the lower-ability characters you can&#39;t hit with the saber, then slice and dice the Jedi that is standing in your way.  Throw in other classic Vader helpers like The Circle Is Now Complete, You Are Beaten and Sniper & Dark Strike and you are looking at a seriously powerful one-man army.  Just like Vader deserves to be.  Just remember to pull out the defensive shield to stop Weapon Levitation from ruining your day.  Not even Jedi Masters are safe from Vader anymore.<br />
<br />
Vader (V) <br />
Power 6, Ability 6 <br />
Deploy 6, Forfeit 8 <br />
Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. Jedi are defense value -1 and forfeit -2 at same or related sites. Once per turn in a battle involving Vader, you may substitute an Interrupt of destiny < 4 in hand for one weapon or battle destiny you just drew. Immune to attrition < 5. <br />
<br />
Forever referred to as &quot;crappy 2-player Vader,&quot; from now on Vader (V) will be referred to as &quot;The Jedi Hater.&quot; Defense value -1 to Jedi is huge, especially in light of the new Darth Vader&#39;s Lightsaber. This means that, is you were to play You Cannot Hide Forever with this Vader (V) and his new saber, you could get to draw 3 destiny and choose 2, and if you manage to draw a total of 6 or better than any Jedi Master will be hit. And drawing a total of 6 or better won&#39;t be that tough when you substitute a destiny-3 interrupt from hand for one of your weapon destinies. So use a destiny-3 from hand, draw a 3, hit any character in the game. <br />
<br />
This Vader persona will always get a battle destiny of at least 3, provided you have the right interrupt in your hand. And he can always get a weapon destiny of at least 3 even if you draw a 0 with his lightsaber. <br />
<br />
Like all Vader personas, this one is a pilot and a darn good one. Also, he can still use his game text to get you a consistent battle destiny of 3 in space. And if light side is initiating battle against you, you get the first &quot;just&quot; action which means you can switch the destiny before light side can affect it with something like the &quot;-3 to destiny&quot; political effect or cancel it with Bright Hope (V).<br />
<br />
<br />
